sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client as Student Client
    participant CORS as CORS + Body Parser
    participant RL as Rate Limiter
    participant Route as studentRoute.js
    participant BCrypt as bcrypt
    participant JWT as JWT (jsonwebtoken)
    participant DB as MongoDB (StudentUser)

    Client->>CORS: POST /api/student/auth/login\n{ username/studentId, password }
    CORS-->>Route: Origin allowed, JSON parsed
    Route->>RL: Check rate limit (10 req / 60 s per IP)

    alt Too many requests
        RL-->>Client: 429 Too Many Requests
    else Within limit
        RL-->>Route: OK – proceed

        Note over Route: Input Validation\nidentifier = username || studentId || id\nRequire both identifier + password

        alt Missing fields
            Route-->>Client: 400 – Fields required
        else Fields present
            Route->>DB: StudentUser.findOne({ username: id } OR { studentCode: id })
            DB-->>Route: user document OR null

            alt User not found
                Route-->>Client: 401 – Invalid credentials
            else User found
                Route->>BCrypt: bcrypt.compare(password, user.password)
                BCrypt-->>Route: match true/false

                alt Password mismatch
                    Route-->>Client: 401 – Invalid credentials
                else Password correct
                    Note over Route: campusId check
                    alt No campusId on account
                        Route-->>Client: 400 – campusId required
                    else campusId present
                        Note over Route: First login check (lastLoginAt == null)
                        alt First login – no lastLoginAt
                            Route-->>Client: 200 – { requiresPasswordReset: true, username }
                            Note over Client: Client redirects to\nPOST /auth/reset-first-password
                        else Not first login
                            opt studentCode missing
                                Route->>DB: StudentUser.save({ studentCode: username })
                                DB-->>Route: saved
                            end
                            Route->>JWT: jwt.sign({ id, userType:"student", schoolId, campusId }, JWT_SECRET, "1d")
                            JWT-->>Route: signed token (HS256, expires 24h)
                            Route-->>Client: 200 – { token: "eyJ..." }
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end

    Note over Client,DB: ── Subsequent Protected Requests ──

    Client->>Route: GET /api/student/profile\nAuthorization: Bearer eyJ...
    Route->>JWT: jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET)

    alt Token invalid or expired
        JWT-->>Client: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    else Token valid
        JWT-->>Route: decoded { id, userType, schoolId, campusId }
        Note over Route: authStudent.js middleware\nattaches req.user, req.campusId
        Route->>DB: StudentUser.findById(id).populate(schoolId)
        DB-->>Route: student document + school info
        Route-->>Client: 200 – { student profile, schoolInfo }
    end
